 became the Mark Twain of all time. This title is part of UC Press's Voices Revived program, which commemorates University of California Press’s mission to seek out and cultivate the brightest minds and give them voice, reach, and impact. Drawing on a backlist dating to 1893, Voices Revived makes high-quality, peer-reviewed scholarship accessible once again using print-on-demand technology. This title was originally published in 1991.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors, Americany19th centuryvBiography. 4aAmerica. 4aAmerican literature. 4aEnglish Literature. 4ahistory of literature. 4ahumor. 4aindividual authors. 4aliterature. 4apoetry. 4apoets. 4apresent. 4awriter. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520348240?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520348240423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520348240/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles